Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural-network-based statistical machine-learning techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses a case study involving a complex input format and a large complex parser, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the tension between conflicting learning and fuzzing goals, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a new algorithm for the learn&fuzz challenge, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
